metadata.title: Alaska Quick Look Landsat Imagery

creators.name: University of Alaska Fairbanks (UAF), Geophysical Institute

metadata.description: Data Type: Remotely Sensed Data;   Alaska Quick Look is black and white imagery taken from Landsat satellites during off hours when the satellites were at oblique angles to the earth. The photos were taken for research purposes at the University of Alaska Fairbanks. Hard-copy photos are available at a cost of reproduction. The photos can be scanned or digitized.
